 readings reimagine religion as a practice that unsettles certainty and develops mutual flourishing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aEarthquakes in literature. 0aEarthquakesxReligious aspects. 0aEarthquakeszCypruszPaphos. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zCypruszPaphos. 0aGardens in literature. 0aMountains in literature. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aJerome, Saint Hilarion, earthquakes, gardens, Cyprus, hagiography, place, religion, saints, late antiquity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107973290 cprintz978022682322540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226824550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226824550/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles